---
# Symphony WORKFLOW.md example (rename to WORKFLOW.md and set LINEAR_API_KEY)
tracker:
  kind: linear
  api_key: $LINEAR_API_KEY
  project_slug: YOUR_PROJECT_SLUG
  # assignee: $LINEAR_ASSIGNEE
  # kind: memory
  # memory_issues:
  #   - id: mem-1
  #     identifier: MEM-1
  #     title: Local test issue
  #     state: Todo
polling:
  interval_ms: 30000
workspace:
  root: ./symphony_workspaces
worker:
  # ssh_hosts:
  #   - worker-a
  #   - worker-b:2222
  # max_concurrent_agents_per_host: 2
delivery:
  spec_driven:
    enabled: true
    required_assets:
      - docs/feature-specs/README.md
      - docs/feature-specs/templates/feature-spec-template.md
      - docs/patterns/spec-to-validation-mapping.md
      - docs/patterns/agent-delivery-handoff.md
      - docs/patterns/security-review-checklist.md
      - docs/runbooks/AGENT_PERMISSION_RUNBOOK.md
      - docs/exec-plans/templates/execution-plan-template.md
      - artemis-symphony/prompts/spec-driven-delivery.md
      - artemis-symphony/skills/spec-driven-delivery.md
      - artemis-symphony/prompts/adversarial-review.md
      - artemis-symphony/skills/adversarial-review.md
      - scripts/harness/check-feature-specs.sh
      - scripts/harness/check-spec-driven-delivery-chain.sh
reporting:
  linear_comments:
    enabled: false
    issue_title_regex: ^进度汇报$
    # success_template: |
    #   Symphony 已完成一次处理尝试：{{ issue.identifier }} / turns={{ attempt.turn_count }}
    # failure_template: |
    #   Symphony 本轮处理失败：{{ issue.identifier }} / reason={{ retry.error }}
agent:
  max_concurrent_agents: 2
  max_turns: 20
  max_retry_backoff_ms: 300000
codex:
  command: codex app-server
  # approval_policy: never
  # approval_policy:
  #   reject:
  #     rules: true
  # thread_sandbox: workspace-write
  turn_timeout_ms: 3600000
  read_timeout_ms: 5000
  stall_timeout_ms: 300000
---

You are working on a Linear issue inside the Artemis repository.

Before changing code, read these minimal repository-local sources of truth:

1. `AGENTS.md`
2. `ARCHITECTURE.md`
3. `docs/agent-workflow/AGENT_DEVELOPMENT_WORKFLOW.md`

Then route by task type and read only the relevant additional assets:

- Quality / progress context: `QUALITY_SCORE.md`, `docs/governance/CHECKLIST.md`, `docs/reports/ROADMAP.md`
- Stable rules: relevant files under `openspec/specs/`
- Existing staged work: relevant active plan under `docs/exec-plans/active/`, if one exists
- Vague request: `artemis-symphony/prompts/agent-requirement-intake.md`
- Business feature: `docs/feature-specs/README.md`, `docs/patterns/spec-to-validation-mapping.md`
- Security-sensitive work: `docs/security/THREAT_MODEL.md`, `docs/patterns/security-review-checklist.md`, `docs/runbooks/AGENT_PERMISSION_RUNBOOK.md`

When the task matches a common engineering pattern, also read the corresponding asset:

- New domain service: `artemis-symphony/skills/new-domain-service.md`
- New Dubbo client: `artemis-symphony/skills/new-dubbo-client.md`
- New ArchUnit rule: `artemis-symphony/skills/add-archunit-rule.md`
- Contract change: `artemis-symphony/skills/contract-change.md`
- Deploy or rollback drill: `artemis-symphony/skills/deploy-drill.md`
- Expand existing service: `artemis-symphony/skills/expand-existing-service.md`
- Business feature or PRD-style request: `artemis-symphony/skills/spec-driven-delivery.md`
- High-risk permission, transaction, concurrency, SQL, logging, or observability change: `artemis-symphony/skills/adversarial-review.md`

Execution rules:

- Treat repository-local docs and specs as the primary source of truth.
- Keep new or updated code comments, config comments, and contributor-facing docs in Chinese.
- Keep identifiers and configuration keys in English.
- Prefer using repository scripts instead of inventing ad-hoc command sequences.
- If the request is still vague after reading the sources above, use `artemis-symphony/prompts/agent-requirement-intake.md` to normalize the需求 before implementation.
- If the request has business rules, data model impact, API impact, internal RPC impact, permissions, or cross-module behavior, use `artemis-symphony/prompts/spec-driven-delivery.md` and create or update a Feature Spec under `docs/feature-specs/active/` before implementation.
- Map every key acceptance criterion to a test, smoke, harness script, or explicit manual validation item before final handoff.
- For permission, idempotency, locking, transaction, exception, SQL performance, logging, or observability risk, use `docs/patterns/security-review-checklist.md` and `docs/runbooks/AGENT_PERMISSION_RUNBOOK.md`.
- Use `scripts/harness/verify-changed.sh` for scoped validation.
- Use `scripts/harness/full-verify.sh` for cross-module or high-risk changes.
- Use `scripts/harness/check-api-doc-sync.sh` and `scripts/harness/check-client-contracts.sh` when touching contracts or API docs.
- Use `scripts/harness/check-critical-path-tests.sh` when adding new guardrails or key-path tests.
- When changing `artemis-system` REST behavior and the service is running locally, use `scripts/smoke/system-lookup.sh`.
- If a task changes stable behavior rules, constraints, contracts, or repository workflow, update the relevant OpenSpec artifacts in the same change whenever practical.
- For complex implementation work, create or update an execution plan under `docs/exec-plans/active/`.
- When a task both changes rules and requires staged delivery, use both: OpenSpec artifacts describe the rule change, and the execution plan tracks implementation, risk, and verification.
- Before the final handoff, answer the self-review questions in `docs/agent-workflow/AGENT_REVIEW_LOOP.md` and use `artemis-symphony/prompts/self-review-and-handoff.md` as the output template.
- For high-risk changes, run an adversarial self-review with `artemis-symphony/prompts/adversarial-review.md` and list the remaining reviewer focus items.
- When the task is Phase-sized or multi-checklist, use `artemis-symphony/prompts/phase-delivery-plan.md` to structure the plan.

Complete the task described in the issue.

**Issue:** {{ issue.identifier }} - {{ issue.title }}

{% if issue.description %}
**Description:**
{{ issue.description }}
{% endif %}

{% if has_attempt %}
This is retry/continuation attempt {{ attempt_number }}.
{% endif %}
